          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Excitation of the giant-resonance region in 58Ni and",
                "208Pb by inelastic scattering of 270 MeV helions"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "S.Kailas",
                "A.Saxena",
                "P.P.Singh",
                "Q.Chen",
                "P.Schwandt",
                "E.J.Stephenson"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "3INDTRM",
                "1USAINU"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,NP/A,499,(2),283,1989",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,NP/A,499,(2),283,1989",
                    "doi": "10.1016/0375-9474(89)90047-X",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "NP/A",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "499",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": "2",
                        "page": "283"
                      },
                      "date": 1989
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "#doi:10.1016/0375-9474(89)90047-X"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAINU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE-IN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scattered helions were detected using a",
                "dE-E telescope consisting of intrinsic germanium",
                "detectors of 1 cm thickness. A rectangular slit of",
                "0.4x1 cm2 placed in front of the detectors defined",
                "the angular acceptance of the detectors as 0.3",
                "degrees in Theta. An overall energy resolution of",
                "600-700 keV FWHM was achieved."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HE3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Using both hardware and software constraints,",
                "we restricted the measurements to cover the",
                "excitation-energy range of O-40 MeV in the nuclei",
                "studied. Whenever the elastic event rates were very",
                "high, signals corresponding to elastic events were",
                "electronically blocked before entering the data",
                "acquisition computer. Data were obtained in the",
                "angular range 7-20 degrees for 208Pb and 7.5-20",
                "degrees for 58Ni targets. Measurements were carried",
                "out in steps of 0.5-1.5 degrees, depending upon the",
                "angular region. In order to obtain clean inelastic",
                "spectra special care was taken to achieve a",
                "good-quality halo-free beam on target. This condition",
                "was periodically checked by replacing the target with",
                "an empty frame. The resulting background counting",
                "rate was minimized before data were obtained at every",
                "angle."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The broad Giant Resonances (GR) structures ride on a",
                "background continuum. In the present work we assumed",
                "the background shapes were obtained by joining",
                "smoothly the data points from the structure-free",
                "excitation region above Ex = 25-30 MeV to the region",
                "below the GR bump at Ex = 7-10 MeV, depending on the",
                "target nucleus.   At these helion-energies cross",
                "sections must be corrected for reaction losses in the",
                "Ge detectors. Rather than estimate the losses, we",
                "have normalized the sigma(theta) values obtained to",
                "earlier, precise measurements made using the IUCF",
                "magnetic spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The main source of uncertainty in the cross",
                "section for GR excitation in the uncertainty with",
                "which continuum cross section can be specified. The",
                "error in cross sections for GR structures varies",
                "between 15-30% depending upon the relative strength of",
                "the GR structure compared to the continuum background.",
                "Besides, normalization procedure led to an uncertainty",
                "of 5 percent in sigma(theta) values obtained here. The",
                "data points have statistical errors of the order of 5%."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " normalization procedure in 5% of sigma(theta)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " of the order 5% and represent the overall",
                "errors from the fitting procedure."
              ]
            }
          ],
